            <h4>What is the current population of Milton?</h4>
            <p>
                Based on the latest 2022 data from the US census, the
                current population of Milton is 2,809.  Milton, West Virginia is the 6,466th largest city in the US.
            </p>

            

            

            <h4>What was the peak population of Milton?</h4>
            <p>
                
                    The peak population of Milton was in
                    2020, when its population was
                    2,822.
                    
                        In 2020, Milton was the
                        6,443rd largest city in the US; now
                        its fallen to the 6,466th largest city in
                        the US.
                    
                    Milton is currently
                        <span style="color: red;">
                            0.5%
                            smaller
                        </span>
                        than it was in 2020.
                    </p>
                
            </p>
            
                
                    <h4>How quickly is Milton growing?</h4>
                
                <p>
                    
                        Milton has grown
                        26.7% 
                        since the 2000.
                    


                    
                        Milton, West Virginia is growing moderately quickly;
                        it is growing faster than 86%
                        of similarly sized cities since 2000.
                    
                </p>
            

            

            

            

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
